{{For|the tantric practice of Prabhashvara|Ösel (yoga)}} '''Prabhashvara''' is the [[color]] of the [[Aura (paranormal)|aura]] of [[Gautama Buddha]].<ref>The Buddhist Channel (D.C. Ranatunga, Sunday Times), April 29, 2007[http://www.buddhistchannel.tv/index.php?id=43,4030,0,0,1,0]</ref> The actual [[spectrum]] of his aura consists of five colors:
* 'nila' ([[Sapphire (color)|sapphire blue]]) * 'pita' ([[Gold_(color)#Golden_yellow|golden yellow]]) * 'lohita' ([[crimson]]) * 'odata' ([[white]]) * 'manjesta' ([[Scarlet_(color)|scarlet]])
The mixture of those five colors is believed to be Prabhashvara but it is depicted as separate strips of the five colors.
